OL,3,CSimon Harris 'hopes' Ireland can drop
OL,4,Clegacy legal case against UK Government
OL,6,FOn Wednesday, Mr Benn told the Commons
OL,7,Fthat the Government was taking the
OL,8,F"first steps" to repeal and replace
OL,9,Fthe Act.
OL,11,FInquests and civil cases will resume
OL,12,Fand the conditional immunity provision
OL,13,Fwill be axed.
OL,15,FHowever, the Government is retaining
OL,16,Fthe ICRIR, which has both
OL,17,Finvestigatory and truth recovery
OL,18,Ffunctions. This has angered some
OL,19,Fvictims, who have demanded that the
OL,20,Fcommission is scrapped and replaced
OL,21,Fwith new legacy mechanisms.
